<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do I prepare for my first plastic surgery consultation?</h3>
<p>Come prepared with a list of your concerns, goals, and questions. Bring any relevant medical records and a list of current medications. Be ready to discuss your medical history and lifestyle habits honestly. This information helps the surgeon recommend the best options for you.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is plastic surgery painful?</h3>
<p>Most patients report that discomfort during the procedure is minimal due to anesthesia. Post-operative pain varies by procedure but is generally manageable with prescribed pain medication. Your surgeon will provide a pain management plan tailored to your specific procedure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does it take to recover from plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Recovery time depends on the procedure. Non-surgical treatments may require no downtime, while minor surgeries may need one to two weeks. More extensive procedures typically require two to four weeks of initial recovery, with full results developing over several months.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Will my results look natural?</h3>
<p>A skilled plastic surgeon focuses on enhancing your natural features rather than creating an artificial appearance. During your consultation, you can review before-and-after photos to understand what natural-looking results look like. Choosing an experienced surgeon like Dr. Manoj K Johar ensures the best possible outcomes.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I go back to work after plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Many patients return to work within one to two weeks after minor procedures. After more extensive surgery, you may need two to four weeks off. The exact timeline depends on your procedure, your recovery progress, and the physical demands of your job.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What are the biggest risks of plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>All surgery carries some risk, including infection, bleeding, scarring, and anesthesia complications. However, choosing a board-certified surgeon and following pre- and post-operative instructions significantly reduces these risks. Discuss all potential risks with your surgeon during the consultation.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do I choose between surgical and non-surgical options?</h3>
<p>Your surgeon will help you evaluate which approach best suits your goals, budget, and lifestyle. Non-surgical options provide subtle improvements with minimal downtime, while surgical procedures offer more dramatic and longer-lasting results. A consultation is the best way to determine the right path for you.</p>
</div>
</div>

